# CLAUDE-CODE-CLI-AGENTS-blueprint — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env`, then source it (or export these in your shell
# profile). Scripts and config templates reference these values.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   $EDITOR .env
#   source .env && export GITHUB_ORG GITHUB_USER TIMEZONE

# GitHub organization or user where your fork lives (and where the scripts
# will look for repos to operate on).
GITHUB_ORG=your-org

# Your personal GitHub handle — used for PR creation, issue assignment,
# CODEOWNERS routing.
GITHUB_USER=your-github-handle

# IANA timezone for cron schedules, digest timestamps, and pipeline timing.
# Examples: America/New_York, Europe/Berlin, Asia/Singapore, UTC.
TIMEZONE=UTC

# Path to the SSH key registered with GitHub (used by bootstrap + delegate).
# Default matches bootstrap-fresh-machine.sh expectations.
# SSH_KEY_PATH=${HOME}/.ssh/id_ed25519_github

# Expected git remote URL for clone-doctor.sh. Override if your fork lives
# under a different org/name than the blueprint default.
# EXPECTED_REMOTE=git@github.com:${GITHUB_ORG}/CLAUDE-CODE-CLI-AGENTS-blueprint.git

# If you run the nightly-puffin pipeline, optionally scope it to specific
# owners (comma-separated). Leave unset to cover your whole GITHUB_ORG.
# NIGHTLY_OWNER=${GITHUB_ORG}

# ─── Morning-digest delivery ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The morning digest is always written to local markdown under
# ${HOME}/.claude/logs/morning-digest-YYYYMMDD.md. Optionally, it can also
# be delivered to email (Gmail OAuth OR SMTP) or a GitHub Discussion. Pick
# ONE of the three blocks below — or leave them all commented out to keep
# digest local-markdown-only (the default).
#
# 1) Gmail OAuth (requires setup-gmail-draft-oauth.sh once per account)
#    Generates a Gmail *draft* for you to review before sending.
# GMAIL_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS_PATH=${HOME}/.config/morning-digest-gmail/credentials.json
# DIGEST_RECIPIENT_EMAIL=your-email@example.com
#
# 2) SMTP (any provider — Gmail with an app password, Mailgun, SES, etc.)
#    Uses msmtp or ssmtp under the hood. Install one of:
#        sudo apt install msmtp  # or: sudo apt install ssmtp
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=digest-bot@example.com
# SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
# DIGEST_RECIPIENT_EMAIL=your-email@example.com
#
# 3) GitHub Discussion — post the digest to a discussion in a tracked repo.
#    Requires the target repo to have Discussions enabled.
# DIGEST_TARGET_REPO=${GITHUB_ORG}/your-ops-repo
